column5: Today I decided to work from home (gotta love software development), and I took a late lunch. Instead of going to McDonalds or cooking up a pot of KD, I grabbed the only two rods I had rigged up, a crankbait and dropshot, and headed down to the bay. With 50k winds out of the West, I was throwing my deep diving crankbait off a point but had nothing to show for it. I moved to the calm side of the point and threw my dropshot about 20ft from shore into 15fow. I let is sit on taught line and gave if a couple jiggles. I had a very light tap and set the hook on this ugly little thing!          http://www.flickr.com/photos/photocentric/
That's one ugly fish.  I wonder if it's a birth defect, or battle scars.
Looks like it ripped off a stringer.  Just goes to show that some fish can take a beating and keep on swimming.
the result of a JPD hookset?
It must of been weird to lip that thing to remove the hooks
Ugly fish. Looks like a predator(movie) fish.lol
Hey Bdow,  When you say the bay what bay are you referring to ? LPB?  Chad
from the looks of that mug, i'd say hamilton bay
Yeah, hammy harbor mutant! I'm guessing it tried to take a bite out of a trolling motor prop!
good god that bucketmouth has been chillin around randels reef too long
Hey,  I was not aware of there being much in the Hammy Harbour? Especially buckets.  Are they easy to target there?  Chad
